  - guidePinDescriptions: one clear line per pin, correct for the verified pinout.
Match the density of a good existing entry — thorough but not bloated. Cut filler.
If you simplify something (propagation delay, metastability, fan-out), say so.

CITE YOUR SOURCES — in the SOURCE CODE ONLY, never in the user-facing text (the
description, guideOverview, guideSections and pin descriptions stay clean per
Manifesto.md — no citation clutter there). In a header comment directly above the
